reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 19, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Does exactly what it claims to do. Saw results very quickly

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 18, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great natural mouthwash!
reviews.reviewText: I bought this product since it contains food grade hydrogen peroxide, and is not tested on animals, but on friends and neighbors. It has a subtle yet refreshing minty taste, and I have noticed that it seems to have reduced any gum inflammation that I had before. It is somewhat expensive for a mouthwash, but I must say, it is worth it. It is best to order 3 or more bottles at a time, to get the best price. I hope that as this company has success, that they will continually lower the price more, and that way more customers can enjoy it. I advise you to try it, as I am sure you will like it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 24, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars So far very pleased with the product
reviews.reviewText: So far very pleased with the product. Can't wait to see if my dentist sees a difference. I did order another bottle.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 12, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Feels like I just came from the dentist
reviews.reviewText: I've been looking for a cruelty-free, preservative-free, peroxide-based mouthwash and am so happy to have found this brand. The mouthwash has a very faint mint taste and you can feel the foaming action in your mouth without the sting of alcohol. Not only does it work beautifully, the mouthwash has been "tested on family and friends, not animals." I highly recommend this product. You have a new customer, Lucky Teeth!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 22, 2021
reviews.reviewText: I was not impressed by this mouthwash. It was tasteless; looked and tasted like hydrogen peroxide. Overpriced. Will not reorder!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 4, 2016
reviews.reviewText: I've only used this for a couple of days so I can't attest to its long-term effects, but so far I love it. The company was wonderful to deal with - my order arrived quickly, was packaged well to insure no leakage, and even came with a sample of their toothpaste. I love that the mouthwash is organic and does not contain things I'm trying to avoid (gluten, fluoride, and other nasty chemicals). It seems like it's really good for your mouth and the taste is pleasant - not too strong. Yes, it's pricey, but you don't use that much at a time and it's worth it.

reviews.reviewText: No way of knowing... only the packaging arrived.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 29, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars love this mouth wash
reviews.reviewText: love this mouth wash. gum disease and tooth decay are hereditary in my family. i have been following the fluoride trend for my whole life and yet it always seemed to land me back in the dentist office more often than not. I have been through one container of this mouthwash along with the original tooth paste and have seen noticeable improvements in teeth regeneration, whiting, breath, and my gums are less swollen and lighter pink. i i use the tooth paste twice a day and one cap full of the mouth wash three times a day along with flossing once a day. love it and cannot wait to see further improvement.
